contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:54.247 --> 01:57.282
- Father... we know

01:57.284 --> 01:59.651
- you are a healer.
- (MAN): Yes, Lord.

01:59.719 --> 02:03.054
- We know you're a deliverer.
- (SEVERAL PEOPLE): Yes, Lord.

02:03.123 --> 02:05.757
- We know you are a way-maker.

02:05.826 --> 02:07.759
- (MAN): Way-maker!

02:07.828 --> 02:11.396
- We know you can
do anything but fail.

02:11.464 --> 02:13.665
- (MAN): It's true, he can!
- (WOMAN): Yes, he can.

02:13.734 --> 02:15.701
- Let your healing
flow through the hands

02:15.769 --> 02:18.503
- of your humble servant.
- (WOMAN): Bless the Lord!

02:18.572 --> 02:20.539
(TREMULOUS BREATHING)

02:22.642 --> 02:25.043
(RISING MUSIC)

02:25.111 --> 02:27.880
♪♪♪

02:38.625 --> 02:40.525
- I can stand!

02:40.528 --> 02:43.061
Oh, Jesus, thank you!

02:43.129 --> 02:45.730
- This man is healed!

02:45.733 --> 02:48.167
In the name of Jesus and by the power

02:48.235 --> 02:50.835
of the Holy Ghost! We have no other God

02:50.904 --> 02:52.671
but you!

02:52.739 --> 02:55.207
Hallelujah!

02:55.275 --> 02:57.042
Hallelujah!

03:02.282 --> 03:04.249
(UPBEAT PIANO MUSIC)

03:04.317 --> 03:06.919
♪♪♪

03:22.035 --> 03:24.469
- Well, I guess today
just wasn't meant

03:24.537 --> 03:27.472
to be my day. Everything
in the Lord's time.

03:27.540 --> 03:30.108
(TENSE JAZZ MUSIC)

03:30.176 --> 03:33.111
♪♪♪

03:40.054 --> 03:42.988
(FAST-PACED JAZZ MUSIC)

03:43.056 --> 03:45.057
♪♪♪

03:50.831 --> 03:52.931
(GRUNTING)
- Hands high, elbows low.

03:52.999 --> 03:54.933
And keep that head moving.

03:54.935 --> 03:57.102
- Moses! You're back!

03:57.104 --> 03:59.771
- Why didn't you say something?
- I just got in.

03:59.839 --> 04:02.474
- What about your
Jack Dempsey fight?

04:02.542 --> 04:05.077
- Not happening.
- Why not?

04:05.145 --> 04:07.078
- The mob turned up. Insisted I
take a dive. They didn't like

04:07.081 --> 04:09.281
- my answer very much.
- I am so sorry.

04:09.349 --> 04:12.517
- That's OK.
- Do you want to come up?

04:12.585 --> 04:15.287
- Well, I wouldn't want to
interrupt with your training.

04:15.355 --> 04:17.822
- Well, I think it's
time for a break.

04:17.891 --> 04:20.825
(SULTRY JAZZ MUSIC)

04:20.827 --> 04:23.829
♪♪♪

04:36.443 --> 04:38.877
- Mrs. Clarke.
- Frankie.

04:38.945 --> 04:40.779
- I, um...

04:40.847 --> 04:44.015
this is Moses Page.
Moses, this is Trudy's mother,

04:44.084 --> 04:46.451
- Mildred.
- Ma'am.

04:46.453 --> 04:50.188
- Mm-hmm.
- What brings you here?

04:50.257 --> 04:53.458
- Oh, I, um...
- I brought you a case.

04:53.527 --> 04:55.394
- Well, I'll let you
get to business.

04:55.462 --> 04:57.462
- Maybe we can chat later?

04:57.531 --> 04:58.863
- Count on it.

04:58.866 --> 05:02.000
- The pleasure is mine, Mrs. Clarke.
- Hmm!

05:04.804 --> 05:06.805
- "Chat later."

05:06.873 --> 05:09.041
That's what they're calling it nowadays?

05:11.211 --> 05:13.145
- I'm telling you Trudy,
Elsie is in danger.

05:13.213 --> 05:15.313
I need you to find her and your
mother says you're the best.

05:15.382 --> 05:19.351
- She is the best.
- Is that one of your employees?

05:19.419 --> 05:21.419
- Not exactly...
- It doesn't matter.

05:21.422 --> 05:25.223
All I know is my daughter is
in danger. You have to find her.

05:25.291 --> 05:27.059
- Don't look at me.
- You're the boss.

05:29.229 --> 05:31.296
- We'll take the case.

05:31.365 --> 05:33.832
- God bless you, girl!

05:36.403 --> 05:39.270
(THEME MUSIC)

05:39.339 --> 05:41.340
♪♪♪

05:43.643 --> 05:45.443
(ENGINE RUMBLING)

05:45.446 --> 05:48.113
- So, a preacher's daughter

05:48.181 --> 05:50.916
walks out of church and just vanishes.

05:50.984 --> 05:53.251
- Maybe someone was waiting
and just nabbed her.

05:53.320 --> 05:55.286
- Why would someone do that?

05:55.355 --> 05:57.356
From all accounts she
was a saint... literally.

05:57.424 --> 05:59.424
- You haven't known
many preachers' daughters.

05:59.493 --> 06:02.026
- Maybe she ran away.
- It can't be an easy burden

06:02.095 --> 06:04.196
knowing that you're hoodwinking
all of those sufferers.

06:04.264 --> 06:06.264
- You haven't seen
what she can do.

06:06.333 --> 06:08.233
- I'm sure she laid
her hands on someone,

06:08.301 --> 06:10.068
they felt like they were healed.

06:10.070 --> 06:12.036
In a few days they'll
be back in a wheelchair

06:12.105 --> 06:14.740
- looking for the next miracle.
- She wants to heal people.

06:14.808 --> 06:16.975
- I'm sure she does.
- All right, look.

06:17.043 --> 06:18.810
I know your instinct
is to think that everything's

06:18.879 --> 06:20.679
a con job, but sometimes it's not.

06:20.747 --> 06:24.315
- When it comes to

06:24.384 --> 06:26.318
defying logic, I think
it's a good instinct to have.

06:28.221 --> 06:30.055
- ♪♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

06:30.123 --> 06:32.957
♪ Ooh ♪♪ (DOOR OPENING)

06:32.960 --> 06:35.927
- Good afternoon. You must
be the ladies my wife hired.

06:35.996 --> 06:38.797
Welcome to Merciful Zion Assembly.

06:38.865 --> 06:42.100
- I'm Pastor Edmund Thompson.
- Frankie Drake.

06:42.169 --> 06:44.669
This is Trudy Clarke.

06:44.737 --> 06:46.504
- What can I do to help?

06:46.507 --> 06:48.907
- Pastor, can you think
of anyone that might want

06:48.975 --> 06:51.476
- to harm Elsie?
- Jealousy and envy

06:51.478 --> 06:53.578
lurk in every corner,
but Elsie's anointed,

06:53.646 --> 06:55.346
protected by the blood of the lamb.

06:55.415 --> 06:57.515
- I am not sure

06:57.584 --> 06:59.918
that you answered the question.

06:59.986 --> 07:02.287
Is there anyone you can think
of that would want to harm her?

07:02.355 --> 07:04.122
- Elsie had no enemies
I know of.

07:04.191 --> 07:06.090
- She doesn't have any
close friends? Or someone

07:06.159 --> 07:08.593
- that might know something?
- Well, my daughter is so busy

07:08.662 --> 07:11.062
doing the Lord's work
she has no time to fraternize.

07:11.131 --> 07:13.131
- She doesn't have any hobbies
or interests outside of church?

07:13.133 --> 07:15.300
- Well, idle hands are
the plaything of the devil.

07:15.302 --> 07:17.335
- What about someone
from church?

07:17.337 --> 07:19.604
Maybe someone was angry
because she didn't heal them.

07:19.672 --> 07:23.007
- Well, I suppose it's possible,

07:23.076 --> 07:25.510
but there's no one I know of. In fact,

07:25.578 --> 07:28.546
Elsie recently began taking on
in-home consultations

07:28.549 --> 07:30.515
to see those she
couldn't help at church.

07:30.583 --> 07:32.484
- Can we take a look
at the list

07:32.552 --> 07:35.053
- of appointments?
- Of course.

07:37.957 --> 07:40.525
- (FRANKIE): <i>OK. Well,
thank you very much.</i>

07:40.593 --> 07:42.894
That is the third person who says Elsie

07:42.896 --> 07:46.164
didn't show up for one of her
private healing sessions.

07:46.233 --> 07:49.834
I don't know what's worse -
false hope or false hope denied.

07:49.837 --> 07:51.836
- So where is Elsie going
if she's not

07:51.905 --> 07:53.838
ministering to the flock?

07:53.907 --> 07:56.508
- Where would a preacher's
daughter hide her secrets?

07:56.576 --> 07:59.344
- Maybe we should
stop thinking of her

07:59.412 --> 08:01.513
as a "preacher's daughter" and start

08:01.581 --> 08:03.815
thinking of her as a teenage girl.

08:10.590 --> 08:13.458
- I'm not buying it.
- Buying what?

08:13.527 --> 08:15.493
- This is not
a teenage girl's bedroom,

08:15.562 --> 08:17.395
it's just staged to look like one.

08:17.464 --> 08:20.498
There's no secrets.

08:20.567 --> 08:22.834
Even her diary. It's...

08:22.902 --> 08:25.603
just filled with bible verses
and poetry...

08:25.606 --> 08:27.605
and it's not very good.

08:27.608 --> 08:30.909
"Now we must part love, I'll ask again.

08:30.977 --> 08:32.744
"Don't let this pleading be all in vain.

08:32.812 --> 08:34.846
"You know I love you,

08:34.914 --> 08:35.813
why not forgive?"

08:35.881 --> 08:38.283
- Those are lyrics

08:38.284 --> 08:40.284
TO A JAZZ TUNE: "Please Say You Will."

08:40.352 --> 08:43.054
- A preacher's daughter
listening to the devil's music.

08:43.121 --> 08:45.490
Maybe there's more to her
than we thought.

08:45.492 --> 08:48.126
- This must be where
she kneels to pray.

08:59.606 --> 09:02.407
- What is this?
- Nice work.

09:02.475 --> 09:04.742
- Hm...

09:04.811 --> 09:07.913
Tobacco, rolling papers,

09:07.981 --> 09:10.882
matches... Sapphire Club.

09:10.950 --> 09:13.118
- That's that jazz club
down on Wellington.

09:13.186 --> 09:16.487
- Looks like Elsie's
got jazz on the brain.

09:16.556 --> 09:19.457
(JAZZ MUSIC)

09:19.525 --> 09:21.660
♪♪♪

09:24.297 --> 09:27.799
- Trudy? I think you need
to check your eyeliner.

09:27.867 --> 09:30.468
- Really?
- Trust me.

09:30.536 --> 09:32.604
- Oh. Right.

09:35.475 --> 09:37.275
OK.

09:37.344 --> 09:39.143
What am I looking for?

09:39.146 --> 09:41.212
- A blue, four door sedan.

09:41.281 --> 09:43.381
- Got it.
- I think it's been

09:43.449 --> 09:45.950
following us since we left the office.

09:46.019 --> 09:48.653
Can you get a license plate?

09:48.721 --> 09:52.156
- 650-857.
- Let's see if Mary

09:52.159 --> 09:54.693
can find out anything for us.

09:57.464 --> 10:00.098
♪♪♪

10:03.036 --> 10:04.970
- No sign of Elsie.

10:05.038 --> 10:07.038
We might as well settle in.

10:07.040 --> 10:09.674
Two colas, please.

10:18.985 --> 10:21.052
- The piano player...

10:21.120 --> 10:23.721
he's also the church pianist.

10:23.790 --> 10:26.658
- Small world.
- Isn't it?

10:26.726 --> 10:28.593
- I guess Elsie's not the
only member of the flock who's

10:28.662 --> 10:30.595
looking for God in strange places.

10:30.664 --> 10:33.632
- ♪♪ ...the way I'm feelin' ♪
- Gotta give it to him.

10:33.700 --> 10:35.934
- ♪ When you squeeze me tight ♪
- He's good on the ivories.

10:36.002 --> 10:37.969
- ♪ Amplify it, baby ♪

10:38.037 --> 10:39.938
♪ Turn that dial to the right ♪

10:40.006 --> 10:42.006
♪ Amplify it, baby ♪

10:42.009 --> 10:44.009
♪ Turn it 8, 9 and 10 ♪

10:44.077 --> 10:47.345
- Trudy... look at the singer.

10:47.413 --> 10:50.782
- ♪ Do it over again
Your wireless transmission ♪

10:50.850 --> 10:52.984
♪ Is in my disposition ♪
- Elsie!

10:53.052 --> 10:54.953
- ♪ The tubes
are gettin' hotter ♪

10:55.021 --> 10:56.821
♪ Lean in and have a listen ♪

10:56.823 --> 10:59.524
♪ The Addison is cookin' ♪

10:59.592 --> 11:02.260
♪ And my crystal set is glistenin' ♪

11:02.328 --> 11:04.962
♪ Amplify it, baby ♪

11:05.031 --> 11:06.931
♪ For me ♪♪

11:06.999 --> 11:08.933
♪♪♪

11:10.904 --> 11:13.171
- I guess we can
rule out kidnapping.

11:13.239 --> 11:15.206
- Healing's not her only talent.

11:15.208 --> 11:17.675
- Thank you.

11:17.744 --> 11:20.045
You all are too kind.
I'd like to thank my band,

11:20.113 --> 11:23.181
and especially my piano man,
Tickles Malone.

11:23.249 --> 11:26.584
(APPLAUSE)

11:26.652 --> 11:28.620
We're just gonna take a short break.

11:34.327 --> 11:36.294
- Ladies.
- Hey there, big fella.

11:36.362 --> 11:38.930
We're just going to say hello to Elsie.

11:38.998 --> 11:41.599
- She's a friend of ours.
- I don't know any Elsie.

11:41.668 --> 11:44.535
- She's the singer
who just walked off the stage?

11:44.604 --> 11:47.538
- You mean Della? I suggest you
go back to your seats and wait

11:47.607 --> 11:50.208
for her to come back out. Excuse me.

11:50.276 --> 11:52.410
- (MAN): Take it back!
- (MAN): Get your hands off me!

11:52.412 --> 11:54.812
- Not until you
apologize to my wife!

11:54.881 --> 11:56.314
(SCREAMING)

11:59.352 --> 12:01.753
- Elsie!

12:01.821 --> 12:04.288
- It's OK. You're all right.

12:04.291 --> 12:06.324
- What happened?
- Someone grabbed me

12:06.326 --> 12:08.159
- from behind.
- Did you see who it was?

12:08.227 --> 12:10.295
- I tried to fight back
but all I could do was scream.

12:10.363 --> 12:12.597
- Your screams are probably
what saved your life.

12:12.665 --> 12:14.899
- Wait.

12:14.968 --> 12:17.301
How do you know my name?
I don't know either of you.

12:17.370 --> 12:18.406
We're private detectives.

12:18.409 --> 12:20.371
Private detectives? What
are you talking about?

12:20.440 --> 12:22.807
- We were hired by your parents.
- Father?

12:22.875 --> 12:25.843
You work for my father?
I am not going back home

12:25.846 --> 12:28.580
- and you can't make me!
- It's OK, just calm down.

12:28.648 --> 12:30.581
- You don't understand.
- My father is probably

12:30.650 --> 12:33.017
the one that did this!

12:39.325 --> 12:41.226
- Elsie, why would
your father do this?

12:41.294 --> 12:43.461
- He's worried sick about you.
- I know he's worried

12:43.530 --> 12:45.596
about me because he needs me
to fill the collection plates.

12:45.665 --> 12:48.599
All I ever wanted to do was sing.

12:48.602 --> 12:50.535
I don't want to be a healer anymore.

12:50.537 --> 12:53.938
- Elsie!
- Tickles!

12:54.006 --> 12:55.273
- Elsie, you OK?
- I'm so glad you're here.

12:55.341 --> 12:58.743
- Sh. Hush. Don't worry.
- I'll make sure nothing bad

12:58.745 --> 13:01.012
- happens to you again.
- No offence Tickles,

13:01.080 --> 13:03.848
but in this case, a piano player
might be in over his head.

13:03.850 --> 13:05.884
- Sorry, who are you?

13:05.952 --> 13:08.352
- These are the detectives
my father hired

13:08.421 --> 13:10.721
- to make me go back home.
- They can't make you go

13:10.790 --> 13:12.557
anywhere you don't want to.

13:12.625 --> 13:15.059
- Tickles is right.
- We can't make you do anything,

13:15.127 --> 13:18.963
but we can tell your father
where you are.

13:19.032 --> 13:21.366
We'll be waiting outside
for your answer.

13:30.142 --> 13:33.077
- Let me take Elsie home
with me. She'll be safer there.

13:33.145 --> 13:35.179
People are always coming
and going. They won't even

13:35.182 --> 13:37.748
- blink an eye when she arrives.
- And you'd be with her

13:37.817 --> 13:40.251
- to make sure nothing happens.
- And while she's there,

13:40.253 --> 13:43.054
I can work on getting
to the bottom of things.

13:43.122 --> 13:45.056
- What about your mother?

13:45.124 --> 13:47.124
- Please. My mother loves Elsie.

13:47.193 --> 13:49.594
There's no way she'd turn her away.

13:49.662 --> 13:51.889
I know it's last minute,
but it just happened.

13:51.892 --> 13:53.030
Stop all the long talk

13:53.099 --> 13:54.918
and just spit out what
you're trying to say.

13:54.921 --> 13:56.200
You have to keep an open mind.

13:56.203 --> 13:58.202
- Are you bothering my head
about the phone again?

13:58.271 --> 14:00.238
- No, it's just...
- I told you before,

14:00.240 --> 14:03.274
I am not getting one
of those infernal things

14:03.276 --> 14:05.610
inside my house.
I've spent my entire life

14:05.678 --> 14:08.012
without one. If people need to
see me they can come to my door.

14:08.080 --> 14:11.282
- This is not about the phone.
- It's about a guest.

14:11.350 --> 14:14.285
- You invite somebody
to stay in this house

14:14.353 --> 14:16.287
knowing how crowded it is already?

14:16.356 --> 14:18.356
- Well, she had
nowhere else to go.

14:18.424 --> 14:20.925
And I know she'll be safer here.

14:20.927 --> 14:23.094
- And I suppose this guest
is here already?

14:23.162 --> 14:26.464
- In the living room.

14:26.532 --> 14:28.900
(BOY GIGGLING)

14:28.968 --> 14:30.935
- Elsie, come on. Let's play.

14:30.937 --> 14:33.037
(ELSIE SIGHING)
I want to play hide and seek.

14:33.105 --> 14:34.906
Please. It's gonna be fun.

14:34.974 --> 14:36.875
- No.
- (GASPING)

14:36.943 --> 14:39.577
- You found Elsie! Oh!

14:39.579 --> 14:42.847
- Her mother will be so happy!
- Wait!

14:42.916 --> 14:45.416
You have to keep this a secret.
There's someone after her.

14:45.484 --> 14:47.652
- What kind of trouble
is this girl in?

14:47.654 --> 14:49.654
- I'm not sure yet.

14:49.722 --> 14:51.889
- No enemy will harm her
under my roof.

14:51.958 --> 14:53.891
- Promise me you'll
keep quiet about Elsie.

14:53.960 --> 14:55.726
Even her parents don't know she's here.

14:55.729 --> 14:57.595
- You think your mother

14:57.663 --> 15:00.064
is some kind of... loose mouth gossip?

15:04.637 --> 15:06.938
- No.
- It's gonna be fun.

15:06.940 --> 15:09.440
- I wanna play hide and seek.
- No.

15:09.508 --> 15:12.610
- Look, I have an airplane.
- Stop botherin' our guest, Baxter.

15:12.612 --> 15:14.812
And you all can go upstairs and start

15:14.814 --> 15:17.248
- getting ready for bed.
- It's early!

15:17.316 --> 15:19.083
- Mom, please!
- There will be no talking back.

15:19.152 --> 15:21.419
Understood? You too, Jacob.

15:21.487 --> 15:23.688
- (BOTH BOYS): OK.
- What?

15:23.690 --> 15:27.125
Mom, I'm not a kid anymore.

15:30.830 --> 15:33.698
- Welcome to our humble abode.
- I wish

15:33.766 --> 15:36.100
that my husband Elroy
were here to greet you,

15:36.169 --> 15:40.037
but unfortunately he's away working.

15:40.040 --> 15:42.039
Listen to me, young lady.

15:42.108 --> 15:43.874
I know your parents raised you

15:43.943 --> 15:45.776
with more manners than that
so pick your bottom lip

15:45.779 --> 15:48.379
from off the ground, stand up

15:48.447 --> 15:50.715
and greet me properly
before I give you something

15:50.783 --> 15:52.616
- to truly pout about.
- I'm sorry.

15:52.685 --> 15:54.885
- Mmm. Now let me explain

15:54.954 --> 15:56.854
how things are going to work
around here. You are not a guest

15:56.856 --> 16:00.458
to be waited on. You will do
your share of the chores

16:00.526 --> 16:02.660
- just like everybody else.
- Chores?

16:02.728 --> 16:04.795
- Yes, chores. Pots and pans

16:04.798 --> 16:07.732
and laundry to begin with.
And I expect you downstairs

16:07.800 --> 16:10.134
at 6 AM in order to help

16:10.203 --> 16:12.136
with the preparation of the breakfast.

16:12.205 --> 16:14.538
Trudy will show you to your bed.

16:14.607 --> 16:16.474
Have a nice night.

16:21.080 --> 16:23.047
- My mother's bark
is worse than her bite.

16:23.115 --> 16:25.883
- Why do you live at home
at your age?

16:25.951 --> 16:27.885
- Well, not all of us
have the luxury

16:27.953 --> 16:29.887
to just run off on a whim.

16:29.956 --> 16:32.490
I have responsibilities.

16:32.558 --> 16:35.193
I'll show you upstairs.

16:38.898 --> 16:41.832
♪♪♪

16:41.901 --> 16:44.568
- I never took you
for a custodian.

16:44.637 --> 16:46.838
- Welcome to the glamorous life
of a musician,

16:46.906 --> 16:49.907
detective lady.
Play three sets, then mop up.

16:49.975 --> 16:51.675
That's the deal if we
want to keep our gig.

16:51.678 --> 16:54.212
- And what's "the deal"
between you and the church?

16:54.280 --> 16:57.114
How does your congregation
feel about a jazz musician

16:57.183 --> 16:58.983
- playing the hymns?
- I play the piano anywhere

16:59.052 --> 17:01.685
people pay me to.
Jazz or gospel, they're all

17:01.754 --> 17:05.356
the same chords. Only difference
is one says I love my lady,

17:05.424 --> 17:07.425
while the other says I love Jesus.

17:07.492 --> 17:09.861
- Do you have any idea
who attacked Elsie?

17:09.929 --> 17:12.063
- None.
- Well, do you believe

17:12.131 --> 17:14.065
- it could be her father?
- I don't know. He sure can

17:14.133 --> 17:16.967
get riled up. You should
see him in a sermon.

17:17.036 --> 17:19.270
- What's the deal
with you and her?

17:19.338 --> 17:21.772
- I know what you're thinking.
- I'm like an older brother to her

17:21.840 --> 17:24.407
- just helping guide the way.
- And you've told her all about

17:24.477 --> 17:26.410
the glamorous life of being a musician?

17:26.413 --> 17:28.412
Like mopping up floors?

17:28.481 --> 17:31.115
- Her parents are stifling her.

17:31.183 --> 17:33.551
Holding her back. She has real talent.

17:33.619 --> 17:35.753
She's gonna be big.

17:35.821 --> 17:38.056
- Just a shepherd dog
looking out for the little lamb?

17:40.126 --> 17:42.560
- Look, I'm no fool.

17:42.628 --> 17:45.763
I stand to see a little
something when she makes it big.

17:45.832 --> 17:48.032
How about we leave it at that?

17:48.100 --> 17:50.568
- If you say so, Tickles...

17:52.638 --> 17:55.273
But for a shepherd dog, you sure
do have some sharp teeth.

18:04.183 --> 18:07.485
- (MARY): <i>I checked the record
of every congregation member.</i>

18:07.553 --> 18:09.453
And let me tell you,

18:09.522 --> 18:11.555
there are many stories.

18:11.624 --> 18:13.591
BUT HERE'S THE MOST INTERESTING:

18:13.659 --> 18:17.027
Pastor Edmund Thompson.
He spent five years

18:17.096 --> 18:19.997
in Kingston Penitentiary
for armed robbery.

18:20.065 --> 18:21.999
- A man of the cloth who's done
hard time.

18:22.067 --> 18:24.001
- Just because the pastor
is a convicted felon

18:24.003 --> 18:26.003
doesn't mean he'd harm his own daughter.

18:26.071 --> 18:27.972
- He was losing his meal ticket.

18:28.040 --> 18:31.542
- Well, maybe he
thought if he scared her,

18:31.544 --> 18:33.711
she'd just give up
the notion of jazz singing.

18:33.713 --> 18:35.713
- Or he was just angry
with her for some reason.

18:35.781 --> 18:38.616
- Any luck tracking the blue
vehicle's license plate?

18:38.684 --> 18:41.185
- No, I'm sorry. It know that it
was stolen from The Annex

18:41.253 --> 18:43.053
- about three weeks ago.
- Can you look into

18:43.122 --> 18:45.022
another suspect for us? His name

18:45.091 --> 18:47.358
- is Tickles Malone.
- Tickles?

18:47.426 --> 18:49.827
- He's a pianist.
- And a hustler.

18:49.896 --> 18:53.498
- Claims that he's only interested
in Elsie's singing career.

18:53.566 --> 18:56.734
- Maybe he's tickling
more than just the ivories?

18:56.802 --> 18:58.703
- Mary!

18:58.771 --> 19:01.439
I'm shocked.

19:01.507 --> 19:04.041
I wonder if Tickles has gotten
Elsie mixed up in something.

19:04.110 --> 19:06.310
- I didn't have
much luck with him.

19:06.379 --> 19:08.879
Maybe you should go
down there and have a chat?

19:08.948 --> 19:11.516
- What makes you think Trudy
will have more luck?

19:11.584 --> 19:13.584
- Because I saw the way
he was looking at her.

19:13.586 --> 19:15.720
- And you?
- It's time to have a chat

19:15.788 --> 19:18.422
with daddy dearest.

19:21.627 --> 19:23.794
- I don't understand how my
prison record is helping you

19:23.796 --> 19:25.729
- find my daughter.
- We already found Elsie.

19:25.732 --> 19:27.765
- Praise God!

19:27.833 --> 19:31.002
- Is she all right?
- Someone tried to attack her.

19:31.070 --> 19:33.337
- What?! Is she hurt?

19:33.406 --> 19:35.239
- She's fine.

19:35.307 --> 19:37.308
- So where is she?

19:37.376 --> 19:39.076
- I can't tell you that.
- What?

19:39.145 --> 19:41.912
You have to. I'm her father.

19:41.981 --> 19:44.548
- I need to protect her.
- Until we know

19:44.551 --> 19:46.584
who tried to attack her,
everyone is a suspect.

19:48.887 --> 19:51.622
- You think because I
have a criminal past,

19:51.624 --> 19:53.558
I'd try to hurt my own daughter?

19:53.626 --> 19:55.726
Let me tell you...

19:55.794 --> 19:57.895
I am a redeemed man.

19:57.897 --> 19:59.830
Like Saul on the road to Damascus.

19:59.899 --> 20:02.433
- And what happens

20:02.435 --> 20:05.269
when your flock
finds out that you're a felon?

20:05.337 --> 20:07.871
- They already know.

20:07.940 --> 20:09.707
I thank God every day

20:09.775 --> 20:12.576
for sending me to prison.
It's where I found the Lord.

20:12.645 --> 20:15.246
My flock realizes I'm not a perfect man,

20:15.248 --> 20:18.582
but that I am an example
of how anyone can be reborn.

20:18.651 --> 20:22.052
- I hope for Elsie's sake
that's true.

20:22.055 --> 20:24.488
(VIOLIN MUSIC)

20:24.556 --> 20:26.657
♪♪♪

20:26.725 --> 20:28.793
(SIGHING)

20:36.469 --> 20:38.502
♪♪♪

20:38.570 --> 20:41.005
- We win!
- Yay!

20:41.073 --> 20:43.174
- Another game!
- Yes, another game!

20:43.242 --> 20:45.142
- You all are having
a little too much fun.

20:45.144 --> 20:47.144
- It's after bedtime.
- Oh please, let us play

20:47.212 --> 20:49.179
- another game.
- (BOTH): Please, please!

20:49.182 --> 20:52.283
- Fine, but then
it's lights out.

20:52.351 --> 20:54.551
- How about you and me, Trudy,
against these two?

20:54.620 --> 20:56.987
- Let's do it.
- But be careful. They cheat.

20:57.056 --> 20:59.623
- No! We're not the cheaters.
- (BOTH): You're the cheaters!

20:59.626 --> 21:01.959
- You cheat!
- No, you cheat.

21:02.028 --> 21:04.361
- No.
- Let's go.

21:04.364 --> 21:07.131
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

21:07.199 --> 21:09.533
♪♪♪

21:17.977 --> 21:20.377
- It won't open.

21:20.380 --> 21:22.246
It's nailed shut.

21:22.314 --> 21:24.715
I used to slip out and shimmy
down the drain pipe...

21:24.784 --> 21:26.183
until Momma caught me.

21:26.251 --> 21:28.218
- How did you...
- There's no tricks

21:28.221 --> 21:30.721
we haven't seen before in this house.

21:30.723 --> 21:33.457
Let's you and me have a little talk.

21:33.526 --> 21:36.427
(SIGHING)

21:40.733 --> 21:43.167
- So, why'd your momma

21:43.169 --> 21:45.436
nail the window shut
on her perfect little angel?

21:45.504 --> 21:48.072
- Because her perfect
little angel

21:48.140 --> 21:51.075
- ran away from home.
- You ran away from home?

21:51.077 --> 21:53.410
I thought you had responsibilities.

21:53.413 --> 21:55.880
- I was 16 and I was in love.

21:55.948 --> 21:57.748
- Where'd you go?

21:57.817 --> 22:00.751
- Adrian Sullivan got me
as far as Port Credit...

22:00.820 --> 22:03.487
- and then I got cold feet.
- Was he cute?

22:03.556 --> 22:05.523
- Cute enough to run away with.

22:05.591 --> 22:07.625
- So, um... why didn't
you end up with Adrian?

22:09.695 --> 22:11.929
- We were so young.

22:11.997 --> 22:14.431
And back then I thought the world

22:14.434 --> 22:16.967
would have ended if we weren't together.

22:17.035 --> 22:19.136
But the world doesn't
end over some fellow.

22:19.138 --> 22:21.872
- Did you get punished?
- You've met my mother.

22:21.940 --> 22:24.241
- Well, and you've
met my father.

22:24.243 --> 22:27.111
- I have.
- I tried to tell him how much

22:27.179 --> 22:29.447
I love jazz, but all he
cares about is the church.

22:29.515 --> 22:32.216
- So you'd do anything
just to sing - even run away.

22:34.953 --> 22:37.121
Was this your idea or Tickles'?

22:37.189 --> 22:39.156
- Mine.
- Really?

22:41.226 --> 22:43.527
- He said I was as good as any
singer at The Sapphire Club.

22:43.596 --> 22:45.396
Said he could help get me in there.

22:45.464 --> 22:47.264
- How'd you two meet anyway?

22:47.332 --> 22:50.868
- I was alone in the church,
just singing some hymns.

22:50.936 --> 22:53.204
He came in, started playing the piano

22:53.272 --> 22:56.273
and it was unlike any music
I'd ever heard before.

22:56.341 --> 22:58.742
He asked me to sing along.
Said I was a natural.

22:58.811 --> 23:01.212
- And that's when you
decided to be a singer.

23:01.280 --> 23:04.415
- I did. There's nothing wrong
with that, is there?

23:04.483 --> 23:06.650
- No.

23:06.718 --> 23:09.220
- I wish my father
saw it that way.

23:11.523 --> 23:14.024
- I have to go out.
- There's work to be done.

23:14.092 --> 23:16.827
Don't try anything, understand?

23:16.896 --> 23:19.229
And if you could
take care of this for me?

23:19.298 --> 23:21.232
- Yeah.

23:28.841 --> 23:31.809
(JAZZ MUSIC)

23:31.877 --> 23:34.145
♪♪♪

23:41.687 --> 23:43.454
- ♪♪ I... ♪

23:43.522 --> 23:45.456
♪ I got a man ♪

23:45.524 --> 23:47.925
♪ Who loves me ♪

23:47.927 --> 23:49.894
♪ Like no one can ♪

23:51.798 --> 23:54.164
♪ Unconditional ♪

23:54.233 --> 23:57.468
♪ And eternally ♪

23:57.536 --> 23:59.503
♪ Mine ♪♪

24:07.579 --> 24:10.080
(CLAPPING)

24:10.148 --> 24:12.349
- Wow. Where'd you
learn to sing like that?

24:12.418 --> 24:16.020
- Church.
- They taught you well.

24:16.088 --> 24:18.355
Hey, I didn't even get your name.

24:18.357 --> 24:21.826
- Trudy Clarke.
- My real name is Chester.

24:21.894 --> 24:23.828
God's given you
a real gift, Trudy Clarke.

24:23.896 --> 24:25.896
- I'm sure you tell that

24:25.965 --> 24:28.032
- to all the gals.
- Absolutely not.

24:28.100 --> 24:30.534
- Isn't that what you
said to Elsie?

24:30.603 --> 24:32.970
- What's she got
to do with this?

24:33.038 --> 24:34.872
- You know she's in love with
you. She'd do anything you ask.

24:34.940 --> 24:36.841
- Elsie's just a kid.
- I've done everything I can

24:36.909 --> 24:39.176
to encourage her. I would
never lay a finger on her.

24:39.244 --> 24:41.678
- That's good to know, but it
wasn't what I was getting at.

24:41.747 --> 24:44.181
Is there any kind of trouble
that you got her into?

24:44.183 --> 24:46.217
Some kind of scheme you're working?

24:46.285 --> 24:48.118
- Is this just because
I'm a musician?

24:48.120 --> 24:50.320
- No. It's because you're
a hustler and bad things

24:50.323 --> 24:52.256
come with the territory.

24:52.324 --> 24:54.458
- I'd never do anything
to endanger her.

24:54.526 --> 24:57.094
- Sure about that?

24:57.162 --> 25:00.397
- Nothing I need to know?
- Nothing.

25:02.268 --> 25:04.635
- Let me tell you something.
- When all this is over,

25:04.637 --> 25:06.904
I strongly suggest that you
sit down with Elsie

25:06.972 --> 25:08.739
and have a long talk about what's really

25:08.741 --> 25:10.741
going on between you.

25:10.809 --> 25:12.977
That's if you care
as much as you say you do.

25:20.152 --> 25:22.953
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

25:24.957 --> 25:27.825
- Oh, Jacob.
- What are you doing up?

25:27.893 --> 25:30.961
- Um... you never
came back upstairs

25:30.963 --> 25:33.931
so I just wanted
to make sure you were okay.

25:33.999 --> 25:36.300
- That's very thoughtful of you.

25:36.368 --> 25:39.570
You're actually just the person
I wanted to speak to.

25:39.572 --> 25:42.005
- I am?

25:42.074 --> 25:45.075
- I, um... I
need a favour.

25:45.143 --> 25:47.110
- I can't help you get away,
if that's what you...

25:47.113 --> 25:49.646
- Oh, I would never
ask you to do that.

25:49.715 --> 25:51.949
- Oh, yeah, then what is it?

25:52.017 --> 25:54.151
- I need you
to deliver something

25:54.219 --> 25:56.453
to someone tomorrow morning.

25:56.521 --> 25:58.322
- Oh...

25:58.390 --> 26:00.524
I don't know.

26:00.592 --> 26:03.060
- This person is worried
sick about me

26:03.062 --> 26:05.629
and I just want them to know I'm OK.

26:05.697 --> 26:07.631
That I'm being well taken care of.

26:07.699 --> 26:10.601
So you'll give that to them for me?

26:10.603 --> 26:14.204
- Yeah, um, I suppose
that should be OK.

26:14.272 --> 26:16.340
- Yeah.
- OK.

26:16.408 --> 26:18.542
- OK.
- OK.

26:18.610 --> 26:20.544
- Take care.

26:22.514 --> 26:24.481
(JAZZ MUSIC)

26:24.550 --> 26:26.550
♪♪♪

26:34.893 --> 26:36.827
(ENGINE STARTING)

26:55.280 --> 26:57.381
♪♪♪

27:00.118 --> 27:02.353
(CAMERA CLICKING)

27:05.090 --> 27:08.359
(CAMERA CLICKING RAPIDLY)

27:17.502 --> 27:19.736
- OK...

27:19.805 --> 27:22.439
This is the man

27:22.507 --> 27:25.208
who was talking with the pastor.

27:25.211 --> 27:27.077
He's also the driver

27:27.145 --> 27:29.446
of the mysterious blue sedan.

27:29.514 --> 27:31.615
- Pleasant looking sort.

27:31.684 --> 27:33.684
- I wonder what he
and the pastor are up to.

27:33.686 --> 27:36.153
How did it go with Tickles?

27:36.221 --> 27:38.622
- He's a charmer. And I told him

27:38.624 --> 27:40.624
what those charms could
do to a certain young woman.

27:40.626 --> 27:42.660
- Did you now?

27:42.728 --> 27:45.495
- I don't think he's
doing anything shady.

27:45.564 --> 27:48.532
But I do still think that
Elsie's holding back on us.

27:48.600 --> 27:51.401
- I wonder if it has something
to do with these two?

27:51.470 --> 27:54.505
- Maybe. I just need
a little more time with her.

27:56.108 --> 27:58.208
(STREETCAR BELL RINGING)

27:58.276 --> 28:01.245
- Oh, Frankie!

28:01.313 --> 28:03.113
Oh, I'm glad I caught you.

28:03.181 --> 28:05.615
That car that's been following you?

28:05.684 --> 28:07.617
I think I have something interesting.

28:07.686 --> 28:09.586
- What's that?
- Well, it has to do

28:09.655 --> 28:13.223
with its colour. I don't know if
you realize this, but 95 percent

28:13.291 --> 28:15.192
of the cars on the road
right now, they're black.

28:15.260 --> 28:17.794
- I had never
thought of that before.

28:17.797 --> 28:19.963
- Well, it's dreary,
isn't it, but it makes

28:20.031 --> 28:22.332
the coloured ones stand out. So I went

28:22.334 --> 28:25.769
to my fellow morality officers
and I said to the gals,

28:25.771 --> 28:28.972
"Gals, keep your eyes peeled."

28:29.040 --> 28:31.475
- And?
- Lavina Gladding

28:31.543 --> 28:33.577
saw a car matching
the description parked

28:33.645 --> 28:35.546
- in the same place several times.
- Where was that?

28:35.614 --> 28:38.281
- Clarence Square, between
Wellington and Spadina.

28:38.284 --> 28:40.817
- The Sapphire Club
is on Wellington.

28:40.820 --> 28:42.919
OK. Mary, can you do me a huge favour?

28:42.988 --> 28:45.455
Can you go down to the club
and talk to the piano man...

28:45.524 --> 28:47.925
- Tickles?
- Tickles, yes. Tell him

28:47.993 --> 28:49.927
to keep his eyes open. OK.

28:58.304 --> 29:00.537
(DOOR OPENING)

29:03.108 --> 29:05.642
- Do I know you?

29:05.710 --> 29:07.978
- Occasionally, I'm
a church-going man.

29:08.046 --> 29:09.880
- Oh. That's where I
know you from.

29:09.948 --> 29:11.948
Well, what can I do you for?

29:12.017 --> 29:14.051
- We need to have a little chat.

29:26.097 --> 29:28.732
- It won't bite you.

29:28.800 --> 29:31.868
Ah. Ah.

29:31.871 --> 29:34.905
Here we go.

29:34.973 --> 29:38.074
(CHUCKLING) Keep going.

29:38.077 --> 29:40.344
There. Yes.

29:42.414 --> 29:44.748
Now, this will

29:44.750 --> 29:47.717
make a very tasty fish head soup

29:47.786 --> 29:50.020
come Sunday. Right?

29:53.658 --> 29:55.459
- Ah...

29:57.763 --> 29:59.696
(SIGHING)

29:59.764 --> 30:01.465
- Momma, you know you need to
see the doctor about that hip.

30:01.533 --> 30:03.667
- I have no time for doctors.

30:08.139 --> 30:10.707
(HUMMING)

30:20.452 --> 30:23.520
(SIGHING)

30:23.522 --> 30:26.390
(GROANING)

30:32.530 --> 30:34.631
♪♪♪

30:39.471 --> 30:41.939
It feels looser.

30:45.010 --> 30:48.345
Oh, praise His name

30:48.347 --> 30:51.314
Praise God and give Him all the glory!

30:51.383 --> 30:53.116
Thank you, child!

30:53.184 --> 30:56.286
Oh, come, boys! Come dance with me.

30:56.355 --> 30:58.154
- Let's get out of here.

30:58.157 --> 31:01.091
- Let's go.

31:01.159 --> 31:03.460
(LAUGHING)

31:03.528 --> 31:06.797
- Vern? Baxter?

31:08.867 --> 31:10.967
- She's too proud to ask,

31:10.970 --> 31:12.969
but she's been wanting that
since you got here.

31:13.038 --> 31:15.505
- I don't know if I actually

31:15.507 --> 31:17.507
heal people. Sometimes it seems

31:17.575 --> 31:20.510
that way and then other times
they just get sick again.

31:20.578 --> 31:23.814
- You give them hope.
- That is helping.

31:27.386 --> 31:29.319
- Trudy, I think I
may have made a mistake.

31:29.388 --> 31:31.988
- With Tickles?

31:32.057 --> 31:35.092
- Yeah, and maybe
some other things too.

31:38.731 --> 31:40.797
- What are you two
whispering about?

31:40.865 --> 31:43.267
- Just girl stuff.
- Hmm-hmm.

31:45.704 --> 31:48.338
♪♪ Whatever my lot ♪

31:48.406 --> 31:50.340
♪ Thou has taught me

31:50.342 --> 31:52.342
♪ To say ♪

31:52.344 --> 31:54.644
♪ It is well... ♪

31:54.713 --> 31:56.846
- ♪ It is well ♪

31:56.915 --> 32:00.617
- ♪ With my soul ♪♪

32:04.622 --> 32:07.624
(TENSE JAZZ MUSIC)

32:07.693 --> 32:10.627
(DOOR CLOSING)

32:10.696 --> 32:13.430
♪♪♪

32:29.448 --> 32:31.415
(DOOR HINGE CREAKING)

32:46.865 --> 32:49.533
♪♪♪

33:05.484 --> 33:07.451
(CURTAINS RUSTLING)

33:19.097 --> 33:21.965
- I'd like to see Mr. Tickles.

33:22.033 --> 33:25.168
- He's in the dressing room
in the back.

33:25.237 --> 33:28.271
- Thank you.

33:35.514 --> 33:38.148
- Mr. Tickles?

33:38.216 --> 33:41.451
This is the police. I know you
are in there now open up.

33:41.453 --> 33:43.920
I'm assuming you're quite decent.

33:43.988 --> 33:45.922
(COUGHING)

33:45.991 --> 33:48.992
(RAGGED BREATHING)

33:49.060 --> 33:50.326
Oh, my gosh!

33:50.329 --> 33:53.329
Who did this to you?

33:53.332 --> 33:55.131
- I don't know his name.

33:55.200 --> 33:57.400
I wasn't gonna tell him nothing,

33:57.403 --> 34:00.070
but he got the letter...

34:00.138 --> 34:02.439
- What letter?

34:02.507 --> 34:04.741
- The one Elsie wrote...
- (GRUNTING)

34:04.743 --> 34:07.277
He... he knows where she is...

34:15.587 --> 34:17.219
♪♪♪

34:17.289 --> 34:20.056
- Thank you.

34:22.760 --> 34:26.329
- So... who is your pock-faced
friend with the blue car?

34:26.397 --> 34:29.266
- I'm not sure
who you're speaking of.

34:32.237 --> 34:34.437
- I followed you to
a warehouse on Logan.

34:34.505 --> 34:36.505
I saw the two of you talking.

34:36.574 --> 34:39.042
- There's nothing wrong
with two people talking.

34:39.043 --> 34:40.610
- No, but there's
a counterfeiting operation

34:40.678 --> 34:43.813
happening at that warehouse,
and that, that is wrong.

34:47.418 --> 34:50.219
Someone in a blue car
has been following me.

34:50.222 --> 34:53.123
I believe the owner of that car
is the same person

34:53.190 --> 34:55.125
who attacked Elsie. So if you
care about her at all,

34:55.193 --> 34:57.427
you'll start talking.

35:01.799 --> 35:04.634
- His name's Lyle Walsh.

35:04.702 --> 35:07.370
We did time together
in the Kingston Pen.

35:07.438 --> 35:09.339
- So you two
are counterfeiting.

35:09.407 --> 35:11.474
- No, no.

35:11.543 --> 35:15.678
Prison changed me.
I gave my life over to God.

35:15.747 --> 35:18.214
So when, one day, Lyle
showed up at the service,

35:18.217 --> 35:20.283
I wanted to believe him

35:20.352 --> 35:22.152
when told me he came
to give himself to the Lord.

35:22.220 --> 35:24.788
- But he had other plans.

35:24.856 --> 35:27.491
- Lyle needed a place

35:27.559 --> 35:30.460
to exchange his counterfeit
bills for real money,

35:30.528 --> 35:32.295
a place that saw cash come and go

35:32.364 --> 35:34.164
and no one would ask questions.

35:34.166 --> 35:36.166
- Where better than a church?

35:38.836 --> 35:41.304
- It started off small enough
that I could almost ignore it,

35:41.373 --> 35:43.606
but he kept pushing for more and more.

35:43.675 --> 35:45.642
Nothing was ever enough.

35:45.710 --> 35:48.378
- So how did the scheme work?

35:48.446 --> 35:50.780
- Every Sunday,

35:50.848 --> 35:53.783
Lyle would exchange his new bills

35:53.851 --> 35:55.718
with money collected
from the congregation.

35:55.721 --> 35:58.788
- Right. And then you'd pass off
the counterfeit bills

35:58.856 --> 36:01.457
because who would suspect a
pastor of using fake money?

36:01.460 --> 36:03.526
- I'm not proud
of what I've done,

36:03.529 --> 36:06.930
but I didn't have a choice.
He threatened to harm my family.

36:06.932 --> 36:09.366
- If you were helping him,
why would he attack Elsie?

36:12.837 --> 36:14.704
- Elsie stole money
from the church.

36:14.772 --> 36:17.974
I think she thought
it was the collection.

36:18.042 --> 36:19.809
- But it was Lyle's
counterfeit money.

36:19.877 --> 36:23.746
- And if the police discover
Elsie with it, they'll be able

36:23.749 --> 36:25.582
to trace it back to the church,

36:25.650 --> 36:27.417
- and then to Lyle.
- And he'd end up back in jail.

36:29.621 --> 36:32.255
(PHONE RINGING)

36:32.323 --> 36:35.158
- Drake Detectives.
- (MARY): [Frankie! That guy]

36:35.160 --> 36:37.093
[IN THE BLUE CAR, HE BEAT
THE STUFFING OUT OF TICKLES.]

36:37.095 --> 36:39.095
- Is he OK?
- [I'M TAKING HIM]

36:39.163 --> 36:42.032
[TO THE HOSPITAL. BUT FRANKIE,
THE GUY KNOWS TRUDY HAS ELSIE.]

36:44.102 --> 36:46.570
(RISING JAZZ MUSIC)

36:55.380 --> 36:57.447
- Planning your next
great escape?

36:57.515 --> 37:00.183
- We know how well
that would go.

37:00.185 --> 37:03.152
I just wish there was a way

37:03.221 --> 37:06.289
- of knowing what comes next.
- Where's the fun in that?

37:10.295 --> 37:12.862
- There's something I've
been meaning to tell you...

37:14.966 --> 37:17.867
I stole some of the collection
money from the church

37:17.935 --> 37:19.736
so that Tickles and I could go away.

37:19.804 --> 37:21.838
- Go away where?
- New York.

37:21.906 --> 37:24.841
It was supposed to buy us train tickets

37:24.909 --> 37:27.744
and a place to live while we
made a name for ourselves.

37:27.812 --> 37:30.213
- Did Tickles know?
- No.

37:30.215 --> 37:33.016
I was going to tell him but I
just never got the chance.

37:33.084 --> 37:36.319
- OK, look. Elsie,
you have to give

37:36.387 --> 37:38.321
that money back...
(AUDIBLE VOLTAGE DROP)

37:38.389 --> 37:41.958
- Now what is going on

37:41.960 --> 37:44.060
- in my house?
- I don't know, Momma.

37:44.128 --> 37:46.029
But please, go upstairs.

37:46.097 --> 37:48.365
- Why?
- Momma, please!

37:51.169 --> 37:53.436
(TENSE MUSIC)

37:53.505 --> 37:55.371
♪♪♪

37:55.440 --> 37:58.308
(GLASS SHATTERING)

37:58.376 --> 38:01.577
- I'm scared, Trudy.
- It's OK. I need you to stay

38:01.580 --> 38:03.579
here with Jacob and Elsie and
not make any noise. Can you do

38:03.648 --> 38:06.249
- that for me, Baxter?
- Yes...

38:06.251 --> 38:08.985
- I can come with you.
- I'm not a kid anymore.

38:08.987 --> 38:10.820
- I know you're not a kid.
- That's why I need you to stay

38:10.888 --> 38:13.990
here and protect Elsie
and your brothers. I'll be back.

38:13.992 --> 38:17.427
- Let's go play
hide and seek, OK?

38:17.429 --> 38:19.429
- (BAXTER): OK...

38:22.333 --> 38:25.335
♪♪♪

38:31.276 --> 38:33.510
(FLOORBOARDS CREAKING)

38:39.417 --> 38:41.584
(GUN BEING COCKED)

38:41.652 --> 38:44.354
(GASPING)
- Give me the girl

38:44.422 --> 38:46.222
and no one else gets hurt.

38:46.291 --> 38:48.291
- You don't want Elsie.

38:48.360 --> 38:50.160
You just want your money back.

38:50.228 --> 38:52.729
- Where is it?
- I got it

38:52.797 --> 38:54.564
right here... (GRUNTING)

38:54.566 --> 38:57.367
(TRUDY CRYING OUT)

39:02.039 --> 39:04.607
(SIGHING)

39:07.145 --> 39:09.446
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

39:09.514 --> 39:11.715
♪♪♪

39:28.600 --> 39:31.568
♪♪♪

39:34.672 --> 39:37.173
(SCREAMING)

39:40.145 --> 39:42.478
(CRYING OUT)

39:42.481 --> 39:44.881
- OH!
- (RAPID BREATHING)

39:44.949 --> 39:47.951
- Where's the girl?

39:48.019 --> 39:51.020
- She climbed out the window.

39:59.898 --> 40:02.265
- Now what's a God-fearing woman
like you doing lying?

40:02.333 --> 40:04.267
- Don't you scold me!

40:04.335 --> 40:06.936
- Where is she?
- I told you she's gone!

40:07.004 --> 40:08.805
AHH!

40:08.873 --> 40:11.441
(SOFT WHIMPERING)

40:11.509 --> 40:13.709
Ah! Ah!

40:13.778 --> 40:15.512
Ah! Ah!

40:15.580 --> 40:18.314
Come back and face me

40:18.382 --> 40:20.984
like the toad you are!

40:23.021 --> 40:25.822
- AH!
- Peekaboo.

40:25.890 --> 40:28.158
(SCREAMING)

40:28.226 --> 40:30.527
Where's my money?

40:30.595 --> 40:32.462
- I'll take you
to the money, I swear!

40:32.530 --> 40:34.998
Just don't hurt the children! (GRUNTING)

40:35.066 --> 40:36.999
(RAPID BREATHING)

40:37.068 --> 40:39.402
- Everyone OK?
- Yes.

40:39.404 --> 40:41.337
- Yeah.

40:41.405 --> 40:43.873
- Yes. We're all fine.

40:43.875 --> 40:47.277
- Jacob kept us safe.
- That cretin has no upbringing!

40:47.345 --> 40:50.013
Coming into a Godly homestead
and acting so unruly!

40:50.081 --> 40:52.215
- We're getting a phone
installed first thing

40:52.217 --> 40:54.150
in the morning, no questions asked.

40:54.219 --> 40:56.586
- I guess it can't hurt...
- if only for emergencies.

40:59.557 --> 41:02.758
- The lights all went out
in the house, and...

41:02.761 --> 41:05.394
Trudy took us all upstairs
and all the kids were...

41:05.463 --> 41:07.363
Dad!

41:07.432 --> 41:10.233
I'm so sorry about all this.

41:10.235 --> 41:12.168
- Sh.

41:12.237 --> 41:14.370
I'm supposed to protect you...

41:14.438 --> 41:16.239
and I failed.

41:16.241 --> 41:18.408
I'm sorry.

41:24.315 --> 41:26.482
- There's, um... there
are some things I have

41:26.551 --> 41:28.618
- to tell you.
- I know.

41:28.686 --> 41:33.022
There're some things
I need to tell you too.

41:33.090 --> 41:35.124
- Everyone OK?

41:35.192 --> 41:38.561
- Yes, I actually
think they are.

41:47.539 --> 41:51.040
♪♪♪

41:51.108 --> 41:53.076
- You're awfully quiet.

41:53.144 --> 41:55.545
- I have some news.

41:55.613 --> 41:57.413
- I hope it's good.

41:57.481 --> 42:00.016
- A promoter from England
wants me to fight in Europe.

42:00.084 --> 42:01.918
- Moses, that's fantastic!

42:01.920 --> 42:04.420
How long will you be gone?

42:04.422 --> 42:06.422
- I don't know.

42:06.490 --> 42:08.424
I suppose it depends on how it goes.

42:08.492 --> 42:11.093
- Well... when do you leave?

42:11.096 --> 42:13.029
- Midnight.

42:13.097 --> 42:16.132
- Well...

42:16.200 --> 42:19.769
then I guess we better
make these few hours count.

42:24.242 --> 42:27.377
- ♪♪ Love lifted me ♪

42:27.445 --> 42:31.547
♪♪♪

42:31.616 --> 42:35.852
♪ Love lifted me ♪

42:35.920 --> 42:38.788
♪ When nothing else ♪

42:38.856 --> 42:41.724
♪ Could help ♪

42:41.793 --> 42:46.929
♪ Love lifted me ♪

42:46.932 --> 42:50.533
- ♪ Ooh, oh, oh ♪
- ♪ Love ♪

42:50.602 --> 42:54.671
♪ Lifted me
- Yeah, love ♪

42:56.774 --> 43:00.343
- ♪ Lifted me ♪

43:00.411 --> 43:02.378
♪ When ♪

43:02.380 --> 43:05.815
♪ Nothing else could help ♪

43:05.883 --> 43:09.885
♪ Love ♪

43:09.954 --> 43:14.991
♪ Lifted me ♪♪

